I have a query that I hope some one on this net can make clearer.

Looking at a Homophonic algorithm (eg. Gunther, Massey, et al), they all
require the source probabilities to be fixed.  My question is:
Is it possible to have a Homophonic coder/decoder that can function
adaptively, ie. the source probilities are updated by the new symbol
frequencies encountered?

Any ideas?
